format

Class FillBox

  • Object
    • format.FillBox

  • class FillBox
extends Object
    A shape of a filled rectangle that can be drawn in its Chars2D buffer. This is also an example of a class that is only used inside its package. Remember, no access modifier means that the code is package-private, so only other classes inside the graphics package can use it.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      FillBox(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2, char stroke)
      Create an instance of a rectangle shape that will be filled with the same character repeated throughout.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      (package private) void draw()
      Draws this filled rectangle shape in its buffer, so that buffer contents can be sent to an output destination later.
      (package private) void setBuffer(Chars2D buffer)
      Set the buffer to draw inside for later.

    • Constructor Detail

      • FillBox

        FillBox(int x1,
        int y1,
        int x2,
        int y2,
        char stroke)
        Create an instance of a rectangle shape that will be filled with the same character repeated throughout.
        Parameters:
        x1 - Horizontal position of the top-left corner.
        y1 - Vertical position of the top-left corner.
        x2 - Horizontal position of the bottom-right corner.
        y2 - Vertical position of the bottom-right corner.
        stroke - The character used to fill all characters within the rectangle.
